<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="180" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,310,1887,1913]" box="[189,310,1887,1913]" pageId="4" pageNumber="180">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1887,1913]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="180" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1887,1913]" pageId="4" pageNumber="180">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[188,1399,1933,1995]" pageId="4" pageNumber="180">
Differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[340,611,1933,1959]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Candolleomyces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="4" pageNumber="180" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="cacao">
<emphasis box="[340,611,1933,1959]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="180">Candolleomyces cacao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of the following characters: broad spores (up to 6.3 µm) with indistinct germ pore, absence of caulocystidia, and whitish evanescent veil.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1159,265,338]" pageId="5" pageNumber="181" type="etymology">
