<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1400,996,1092]" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">
According to the taxonomy of 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith A. H." box="[579,743,996,1022]" pageId="8" pageNumber="184" pagination="1 - 633" refId="ref4979" refString="Smith A. H. 1972. The North American species of Psathyrella. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 24: 1 - 633." type="journal article" year="1972">Smith (1972)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Asif &amp; Izhar &amp; Niazi &amp; Khalid, 2022" authorityName="Asif &amp; Izhar &amp; Niazi &amp; Khalid" authorityYear="2022" box="[761,905,996,1022]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Candolleomyces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="184" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="asiaticus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[761,905,996,1022]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">C. asiaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[918,1015,996,1022]" pageId="8" pageNumber="184" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Romagn.)" baseAuthorityName="Romagn." class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Psathyrella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="184" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="section" section="Subatratae">
<emphasis box="[1168,1302,996,1022]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">Psathyrella</emphasis>
section 
<emphasis box="[189,318,1031,1057]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">Subatratae</emphasis>
(Romagn.)
</taxonomicName>
ex Sing, emended in having an evanescent veil, small basidiospores (5–10 µm long), and absence of pleurocystidia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[187,1399,1131,1404]" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">
The ITS sequences of 
<taxonomicName authority="Asif &amp; Izhar &amp; Niazi &amp; Khalid, 2022" authorityName="Asif &amp; Izhar &amp; Niazi &amp; Khalid" authorityYear="2022" box="[474,618,1132,1158]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Candolleomyces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="184" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="asiaticus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[474,618,1132,1158]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">C. asiaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[631,727,1132,1158]" pageId="8" pageNumber="184" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
showed 99.8% similarity with sequences from Indian specimens (GenBank accession numbers 
<accessionNumber box="[678,806,1167,1193]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/KP686449" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">KP686449</accessionNumber>
, 
<accessionNumber box="[819,948,1167,1194]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/KP686452" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">KP686452</accessionNumber>
, 
<accessionNumber box="[960,1092,1167,1194]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/KR154976" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">KR154976</accessionNumber>
, and 
<accessionNumber box="[1155,1285,1167,1194]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/KR154977" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">KR154977</accessionNumber>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1311,1381,1167,1193]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1342,1368]" captionTargetBox="[365,1398,267,1299]" captionTargetId="figure-75@4.[189,1398,263,1304]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Molecular phylogenetic placement of Candolleomyces asiaticus M.Asif, A.Izhar, Niazi &amp; Khalid sp. nov. based on maximum likelihood (ML) method of nrITS sequences." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795499/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). These specimens formed a well-supported clade with the Pakistani specimens analyzed in this study, clearly distinguishable from other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[704,898,1237,1263]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Candolleomyces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="184" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[704,898,1237,1263]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">Candolleomyces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The sequences 
<accessionNumber box="[1088,1216,1237,1264]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/KR154976" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">KR154976</accessionNumber>
and 
<accessionNumber box="[1270,1398,1237,1264]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/KR154977" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">KR154977</accessionNumber>
correspond to the vouchers BAB-4747 and BAB-4748 respectively, and 
<accessionNumber box="[1079,1205,1272,1298]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/KP686449" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">KP686449</accessionNumber>
and 
<accessionNumber box="[1271,1396,1272,1299]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/KP686452" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">KP686452</accessionNumber>
correspond to the vouchers BAB-4772 and BAB-4775 named as 
<taxonomicName box="[943,1169,1307,1333]" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">
<emphasis box="[943,1077,1307,1333]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">Psathyrella</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in GenBank. These Indian collections should be also recognized as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Asif &amp; Izhar &amp; Niazi &amp; Khalid" authorityYear="2022" box="[756,895,1343,1369]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Candolleomyces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="184" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="asiaticus">
<emphasis box="[756,895,1343,1369]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">C. asiaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on our phylogenetic study, but their morpho-anatomical characteristics need to be studied and confirmed in future studies.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[188,1401,1443,1716]" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">
In phylogenetic analysis, 
<taxonomicName authority="Asif &amp; Izhar &amp; Niazi &amp; Khalid, 2022" authorityName="Asif &amp; Izhar &amp; Niazi &amp; Khalid" authorityYear="2022" box="[499,809,1443,1469]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Candolleomyces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="184" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="asiaticus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[499,809,1443,1469]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">Candolleomyces asiaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[817,910,1444,1470]" pageId="8" pageNumber="184" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
reveals to be close relative of 
<emphasis box="[1286,1401,1444,1470]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">
<taxonomicName box="[1286,1395,1444,1470]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Candolleomyces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="184" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="cacao">C. cacao</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
a species described from 
<collectingCountry box="[499,619,1479,1505]" name="Sao Tome and Principe" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">São Tomé</collectingCountry>
(Africa), but the latter has significant morphological differences such as convex to broadly convex pileus, smaller in diameter (
<quantity box="[924,1061,1514,1541]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="184" unit="cm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.5">0.5–1.5 cm</quantity>
), lack of partial veil, smaller basidiospores (5.7–6.8 × 3.5–4.8 µm) and frequent occurrence of caulocystidia (
<bibRefCitation author="Desjardin D. E. &amp; Perry B. A." pageId="8" pageNumber="184" pagination="359 - 391" refId="ref4333" refString="Desjardin D. E. &amp; Perry B. A. 2016. Dark-spored species of Agaricineae from Republic of Sao Tome and Principe, West Africa. Mycosphere 7 (3): 359 - 391. https: // doi. org / 10.5943 / mycosphere / 7 / 3 / 8" type="journal article" year="2016">Desjardin &amp; Perry 2016</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Asif &amp; Izhar &amp; Niazi &amp; Khalid, 2022" authorityName="Asif &amp; Izhar &amp; Niazi &amp; Khalid" authorityYear="2022" box="[275,586,1584,1610]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Candolleomyces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="184" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="asiaticus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[275,586,1584,1610]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">Candolleomyces asiaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[596,689,1585,1611]" pageId="8" pageNumber="184" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is also phylogenetically related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. Bau &amp; J. Q. Yan" authorityYear="2021" box="[1118,1267,1584,1611]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Candolleomyces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="184" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="subcacao">
<emphasis box="[1118,1267,1584,1611]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">C. subcacao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
